HEADWORD: Sea mud
<hw>Sea" mud`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A rich slimy deposit in salt
marshes and along the seashore, sometimes used as a manure; -- called
also <altname>sea ooze</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seamy</ent>⟦br⟧
